Stock

Class Store

  • java.lang.Object
    • Stock.Store

  • public class Store
extends java.lang.Object
    This class represents an object for the store itself. Adopts the Singleton pattern to avoid multiple instantiation of the same object. Contains at least the following properties: (Capital, Inventory, Name)
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Kwun Hyo Lee & Jonathan Wai

      • openAndParseItemsList

        public static void openAndParseItemsList(java.lang.String filePath)
                                  throws CSVFormatException
        Opens csv file from given file path and creates an object for each item with it's specified properties. If an item already exists in itemsList, it updates the properties of the existing item instead of creating a new Item object. Adds all objects to the store inventory.
        Parameters:
        filePath - Absolute path to CSV file containing item properties
        Throws:
        CSVFormatException - Throws exception if the number of rows is more or less than the number of defined columns.
